cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.IT. 

This paper is primarily focused on database-related topics, specifically the discovery of acyclic schemes and multivalued dependencies from data. Therefore, cs.DB is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses machine learning applications, which could potentially place it in cs.LG or cs.AI. The use of information theory in the definition of approximation suggests cs.IT as a possible sub-category. Finally, the scalability experiments could also be relevant to cs.DS.
